{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584050","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584050"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:36:47+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:36:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14333"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14333","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14333"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0,0,0,1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7028"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71442"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7028","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7028"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14333"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56951"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"40"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3618"},{"type":"tags","id":"4340"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"10624"},{"type":"tags","id":"10625"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"16723"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20225"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71442","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71442"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman is in her first trimester of pregnancy. Her obstetrician explains the importance of the placenta in maintaining a healthy pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a primary function of the placenta during early pregnancy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Synthesis of thyroid hormones","Secretion of oxytocin","Synthesis of cortisol","Production of antidiuretic hormone","Production of human chorionic gonadotropin"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary function of the placenta during early pregnancy is the \u003Cstrong\u003Eproduction of human chorionic gonadotropin\u003C/strong\u003E (hCG). This hormone is crucial for maintaining the corpus luteum, promoting it to secrete progesterone, which continues until the placenta takes over this role later in pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are incorrect:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESynthesis of cortisol\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily performed by the adrenal glands, not the placenta.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESecretion of oxytocin\u003C/strong\u003E is by the posterior pituitary gland following its synthesis in the hypothalamus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProduction of antidiuretic hormone\u003C/strong\u003E (ADH) occurs in the hypothalamus and is then released from the posterior pituitary gland.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESynthesis of thyroid hormones\u003C/strong\u003E is carried out by the thyroid gland, not the placenta.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe placenta has several other important functions throughout pregnancy, including gas exchange, nutrient transfer, and waste removal between maternal and foetal circulations. It also produces other hormones such as oestrogen and progesterone later in pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The placenta produces human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG) to maintain the corpus luteum during early pregnancy.","The placenta synthesises oestrogen and progesterone to support pregnancy after the first trimester.","The placenta facilitates gas exchange, nutrient transfer, and waste removal between maternal and foetal circulations."],"references":["Nwabuobi C, Arlier S, Schatz F, Guzeloglu-Kayisli O, Lockwood CJ, Kayisli UA. hCG: Biological Functions and Clinical Applications. Int J Mol Sci. 2017 Sep 22;18(10):2037. doi: 10.3390/ijms18102037. PMID: 28937611; PMCID: PMC5666719.","Soma-Pillay P, Nelson-Piercy C, Tolppanen H, Mebazaa A. Physiological changes in pregnancy. Cardiovasc J Afr. 2016 Mar-Apr;27(2):89-94. doi: 10.5830/CVJA-2016-021. PMID: 27213856; PMCID: PMC4928162.","Betz D, Fane K. Human Chorionic Gonadotropin. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK532950/","Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56951"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14333"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56951","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56951"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-18T16:08:06+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-18T16:08:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7028"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71442"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"40","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/40"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\u2699\ufe0f","name":"Physiology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"de